author: Russell Brand
description:
Looking back at Princess Diana’s death raises more questions than answers. From secret phone taps to ignored evidence, vanished CCTV, and witnesses silenced, the official story falls apart under scrutiny. Whether it’s the landmine campaign threatening powerful interests or the note Diana herself wrote predicting a staged car crash, the pattern is chillingly familiar. Just like with Epstein or COVID, trust in government collapses when the people in power control the evidence—and the cover-up becomes more obvious than the crime.
